4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS REGARDING LEGISLATIVE PRIVILEGE OVER
5 CERTAIN PUBLIC INFORMATION; PROVIDING THAT LEGISLATIVE BILL DRAFTING FILES ARE PUBLIC
6 RECORDS; PROVIDING THAT THE LEGISLATIVE PRIVILEGE ESTABLISHED BY THE SPEECH OR
7 DEBATE CLAUSE IN THE MONTANA CONSTITUTION IS A PROTECTION AGAINST CERTAIN
8 PROSECUTIONS BUT IS NOT A COMPLETE PROTECTION FROM DISCLOSURE UNDER PUBLIC
9 RECORDS LAWS; PROVIDING THAT AN INDIVIDUAL LEGISLATOR'S PRIVATE WRITINGS OR
10 DOCUMENTS ARE PROTECTED FROM DISCLOSURE UNDER PUBLIC RECORDS LAWS; PROVIDING
11 THAT AN INDIVIDUAL LEGISLATOR'S COMMUNICATIONS WITH THE LEGISLATOR'S PERSONAL STAFF
12 ARE PROTECTED FROM DISCLOSURE UNDER PUBLIC RECORDS LAWS; PROVIDING THAT A
13 LEGISLATOR WAIVES THE PROTECTION FROM DISCLOSURE BY SHARING WRITINGS, DOCUMENTS,
14 OR COMMUNICATIONS WITH ANOTHER PERSON; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; AND PROVIDING AN
15 IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE DATE.”
16
17 WHEREAS, Montana has a deeply rooted commitment to the transparency and accountability of
18 government, as demonstrated by the protections offered by the right to know in Article II, section 9, and the
19 right of participation in the operations of government agencies in Article II, section 8, of the Montana
20 Constitution; and
21 WHEREAS, the Montana Constitution has enshrined access to public information in the right to know in
22 Article II, section 9, which states that "No person shall be deprived of the right to examine documents or to
23 observe the deliberations of all public bodies or agencies of state government and its subdivisions, except in
24 cases in which the demand of individual privacy clearly exceeds the merits of public disclosure"; and
25 WHEREAS, the right of participation in Article II, section 8, of the Montana Constitution also ensures
26 that the public must be given a reasonable opportunity to participate in the operation of government agencies
27 prior to the final decision as may be provided by law; and
28 WHEREAS, these fundamental rights are the foundation on which every Montanan is able to exercise
