7 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Legislative bill drafting files -- privileged content -- definitions. (1)
8 Legislative bill drafting files are public records as defined in 2-6-1002 and must be provided upon request
9 pursuant to Title 2, chapter 6, part 10.
10 (2) A legislative bill drafting file contains the history of the drafting, preparation, and process from
11 request to introduction of a bill draft. The contents of a bill drafting file may include but are not limited to:
12 (a) draft versions of a bill prior to introduction;
13 (b) bills or laws from other states;
14 (c) uniform acts or model legislation from any source;
15 (d) reports, articles, papers, or any other research conducted on the topic of the bill draft;
16 (e) legal analysis;
17 (f) e-mails and other communications between the legislator and the bill drafter;
18 (g) e-mails and other communications between the bill drafter and any third party, whether or not
19 the legislator was included in those communications; and
20 (h) any other resources or materials collected or compiled during the course of drafting the bill.
21 (3) (a) The legislative privilege granted under Article V, section 8, of the Montana constitution to a
22 legislator is an immunity from prosecution in a criminal or civil action for the legislator's legitimate legislative
23 acts. The records, including communications, contained in a legislative bill drafting file may not be used as
24 evidence of legislative acts in a judicial proceeding against a legislator.
25 (b) The legislative privilege granted under Article V, section 8, of the Montana constitution to a
26 legislator as it pertains to legislative bill drafting files does not create a privilege of confidentiality against
27 disclosure under Article II, section 9, of the Montana constitution and Title 2, chapter 6, parts 10 through 12, for
28 any communications or other records that are generated in the course of drafting a bill, shared with another
